sections.Learning outcomes:
On successful completion of the course the student will be able to:

Knowledge and understanding
• account for the development of human behavior and social experience in relation to communication media;
• distinguish different communication technologies and relate them to different historical periods;
• explain key concepts and theories in communication technology;

Competence and skills
• apply theoretical concepts and approaches to analyse and compare the practical uses of different communication technologies in various social activities;

Judgement and approach
• reflect upon the way technology changes;
• discuss how technology aids human communication in various social activities;
• constructively criticize methodologies and approaches to the study of communication technology.

sections.Course content:
The course provides students with knowledge of the historical development and social significance of communication technology. The course also familiarizes the students with academic laboratory work in communication technology, and motivates students for future studies within communication technology. The content includes:
• introduction to the historical development of communication technology and different types of communication technology;
• description and discussion of the relation between technology, communication and social activities;
• laboratory experience of communication technology;
• theoretical and empirical analysis of communication technology in personal and professional communication contexts.
